On Ubuntu/Debian (apt):

sudo apt install imagemagick -y

Verify installation:

rpm -qa | grep ImageMagick      # RHEL-based
dpkg -l | grep imagemagick      # Debian-based

ğŸ“‚ Step 2: Download an Image

Example:

    Open browser â†’ Google Images â†’ Save an image (e.g., penguin.png) to Desktop.

    Navigate to directory:

    cd ~/Desktop
    ls -l

    You should see your image file.

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Step 3: Open the Image

Use the display command:

